George North's stunning four-try blitz catapulted Northampton to a bonus-point win at Franklin’s Gardens last night, but Luther Burrell gave England another injury scare as he went off with damage to his left hand.

The Saints ignited their Champions Cup campaign courtesy of North’s heroics and in the process became the first team to beat the Ospreys this season. 

While their Welsh wing provided the deadly finishing, the hosts were also well served by their England contingent, especially flankers Calum Clark and Tom Wood, and lock Courtney Lawes, while fly-half Stephen Myler ran the show with calm authority.

