With the national squad going into camp this evening, head coach Stuart Lancaster will anxiously await updates on Burrell, who was withdrawn just after half-time and was due to go for an X-ray. 

England already have a long casualty list and they could do without losing another centre, after learning that Manu Tuilagi will miss the whole QBE series of four Tests.

Jim Mallinder, Northampton’s director of rugby, said: ‘Luther has banged his hand, it’s very sore and he’s struggling to grip. Fingers crossed there’s no permanent damage.’

