After the break, the 22-year-old smashed over from close range and, three minutes from time, he stole the ball out wide for a superb solo effort — kicking ahead and winning the race to touch down.

‘It’s the first time I’ve scored four tries in a game, so I’m very happy with my performance,’ said North. 

‘That performance was definitely up there for me personally, but it was a whole team effort — we knew we needed a big performance and that’s what we produced.’

